From L – R shows: Oluyemi Obadare, Business Continuity Manager, Information Security, The Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE); Kemi DaSilva-Ibru, Founder, Women at Risk International Foundation (WARIF); and Olumide Orojimi, Head, Corporate Communications, NSE during the presentation of the proceeds from the NSE Employee Giveback Initiative at the WARIF Centre on Friday, 24 January 2020.  About The Nigerian Stock Exchange: The Nigerian Stock Exchange services the largest economy in Africa and is championing the development of Africa’s financial markets.  The NSE, a registered company limited by guarantee, was founded in 1960 and it is licensed under the Investments and Securities Act (ISA) and is regulated by the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) of Nigeria. The Exchange offers listing and trading services, licensing services, market data solutions, ancillary technology services and more.  